TWO men were killed while another suffered moderate injuries after a bakkie collided with a tree on Delfos Boulevard, Vanderbijlpark, on Sunday, 5 June. ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said paramedics were on the scene at 12.33pm, along with the Emfuleni Fire personnel and cops. “One male patient was found sitting up against another tree away from the vehicle having self-extricated. “He was found to have suffered moderate injuries and was treated and transported to hospital,” Meiring said. He said two adult men were found trapped in the bakkie showing no signs of life. “They were both declared dead on arrival by ER24. Emfuleni Fire personnel were on hand for the extraction of the deceased. “The details surrounding the incident are unknown by ER24. However, the cops were on the scene for further investigation,” Meiring said.